# Real-time Transaction Audit Log System

A full-stack fintech application with Django REST API backend and React frontend. Features atomic transactions, real-time balance updates, and comprehensive audit logging for all transfers (SUCCESS/FAILED).

[![Django](https://img.shields.io/badge/Django-4.2-green)](https://www.djangoproject.com/) [![React](https://img.shields.io/badge/React-18-blue)](https://react.dev/) [![PostgreSQL](https://img.shields.io/badge/PostgreSQL-15-purple)](https://www.postgresql.org/)

## ğŸ¯ Project Overview

**Assignment**: Build a real-time transaction audit log system that tracks all money transfers between users with atomic operations and comprehensive logging.

**Implementation**:
- **Backend**: Django REST Framework with PostgreSQL
- **Frontend**: React with Vite, Tailwind CSS, real-time dashboard
- **Key Features**:
  - Atomic transfers (debit sender â†’ credit receiver â†’ audit log)
  - Real-time balance updates
  - Audit trail for ALL transactions (SUCCESS + FAILED)
  - No authentication (demo-ready)

## ğŸš€ Quick Start (5 minutes)

### Prerequisites
- Python 3.10+
- Node.js 18+
- PostgreSQL 15+ (or SQLite for dev)

### 1. Clone & Setup Backend
git clone https://github.com/ayaz1017/-Real-time-Transaction-Audit-Log-System.git
cd "-Real-time-Transaction-Audit-Log-System"
cd core
python -m venv venv

Windows
venv\Scripts\activate

Linux/Mac
source venv/bin/activate
pip install -r requirements.txt
python manage.py migrate
python manage.py createsuperuser
python manage.py runserver

text

### 2. Setup Frontend (New Terminal)
cd ../transaction-ui
npm install
npm run dev

text

### 3. Access
- **Backend**: http://127.0.0.1:8000
- **Frontend**: http://localhost:5174
- **Admin**: http://127.0.0.1:8000/admin

## ğŸ“‹ API Documentation

| Endpoint | Method | Params | Description |
|----------|--------|--------|-------------|
| `/api/accounts/` | GET | - | List all user accounts |
| `/api/audit-log/?user_id=USR001` | GET | `user_id` | User transaction history |
| `/api/transfer/` | POST | `{ "sender": "USR001", "receiver": "USR002", "amount": 200 }` | Atomic transfer |

**Sample POST request**:
curl -X POST http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/transfer/
-H "Content-Type: application/json"
-d '{"sender": "USR001", "receiver": "USR002", "amount": 200}'

text

**Test in Browser**:
- `http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/accounts/`
- `http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/audit-log/?user_id=USR001`

